The Nigeria Security and Civil Defense Corps, Enugu Command, has assured the people of a crime-free Christmas and New Year celebrations in the state. The NSCDC gave the assurance in a statement signed by the NSCDC Public Relations Officer (PRO) Denny Iwuchukwu in Enugu on Thursday. Iwuchukwu said the Corps commandant, Mr Everestus Obiyo, stated this while addressing Heads of Department, Units, Area Commanders and Divisional Officers in the 17 Local Government Areas of the state. Obiyo said that adequate arrangements had been made to ensure that criminal elements in the state would have no room to operate during the season. ALSO READ: NSCDC arrests 2 herdsmen for destroying farmlands in Ekiti Yuletide: Gombe gov directs immediate payment of December… Yuletide: Lagos, Ogun will be crime-free ― AIG Zone 2 Power minister assures Nigerians of power supply during… ICPC secures interim forfeiture order on assets owned by… The commandant explained that the flashpoints and difficult terrains that served as criminal hideouts had been marked and adequate surveillance mounted to stop any untoward act. According to him, all the entrance and exit points in the state are under close watch, with a view to monitoring the movement and activities of the people. ” Full deployment of officers and men of the command had been made and all the personnel on annual leave have been recalled to ensure that all hands are on deck,” he said. The command reminded the people to be security-conscious and not to be carried away by the joy of the season. He noted that criminals always target unguided moments to unleash mayhem to unsuspecting members of the public. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
